[2] Massachusetts (Middlesex county): fox, human exposure
Date: Wed 2 May 2018 9:54 AM EDT
Source: Boston 25 News [edited]
https://www.fox25boston.com/news/2-treated-for-rabies-after-fox-attacks-in-burlington/742286441


A possibly rabid fox is dead after attacking several residents in a Burlington neighborhood [Middlesex county].

[AL] was walking 10-year-old daughter, to the bus stop when the animal charged at them. "It took off and started running toward us, so I stuck her behind me and told her to start getting back to the house, and it started it was lunging and so I was kicking at it, swinging the backpack," [AL] said.

Across the street, [JB] was on the phone with Animal Control after she had been attacked just minutes prior. "I had a Wiffle Ball bat over there and I was just trying to take the water off the tarp and I was poking it like that, and I heard a noise behind me and I had the bat in my hand and I just turned around and the thing came lunging at me and I had to just keep whacking it with the bat," [JB] said.

The Leopold Street neighborhood was frantic with this fox running after people just as many were starting their days.

"Lunged at me, bit me, took me down, it bit me again. While I was down, I kicked it off me and finally got into the house," [AL] said. [Her daughter] made it inside the home, and [AL's] husband came out with an ice scraper to scare the fox off.

Several hours later on a nearby street, another woman was attacked and received injuries serious enough to require a trip to the hospital.

The fox's day came to an end when it attacked a police officer working a detail. "The animal charged at the officer and the officer had to discharge his weapon, and put the animal down," Det Jim Tigges said.

Both bitten women are receiving rabies treatments while the animal is at a lab being tested.

